          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 10 in. by 6 3/4, consisting of 90 leaves, some of which are
                        much torn, especially foll. 46, 55, 56, 60—62, 68, 69, and 90. The quires,
                        13 in number, are signed with letters, from ܐ to ܘ and from ܗ to ܝܐ. Leaves
                        are wanting after foll. 55, 61, 67, and 89. There are from 21 to 28 lines in
                        each page.</p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="chart">
                <extent>
                  <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="90">90 ff.</measure>
                </extent>
                <foliation/>
                <collation/>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Paper, about 10 in. by 6 3/4, consisting of 90 leaves, some of which are
                        much torn, especially foll. 46, 55, 56, 60—62, 68, 69, and 90. The quires,
                        13 in number, are signed with letters, from ܐ to ܘ and from ܗ to ܝܐ. Leaves
                        are wanting after foll. 55, 61, 67, and 89. There are from 21 to 28 lines in
                        each page.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="2">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="major" script="syr">
                <desc>This volume is written in a regular, though rather inelegant hand, of the
                  earlier part of the xiiith cent. (see below, and compare <bibl>Add 14,707<ptr target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/573"/>
                  </bibl>).</desc>
              </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="mixed">
                <desc>See additions.
                 </desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote xml:id="decoNote1" type="illustration hmml:drawing"/>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus/>
                  <p>A later hand has marked the quires with Coptic arithmetical figures (beginning
                    at fol. 24), and has also numbered the leaves from fol. 24 to 54</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="46a"/>
                  <p>On fol. 46 a there remains part of an Arabic note, which seems to date from the
                    year 154—, A.D. 123—, and to have been written by a priest named <persName>‘Abd
                      al-Masīh ibn Sim’ān</persName>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="ar">بس[م الله.....] لما كان [سنة الف] وخمس ميه ..... واربعين
                      [سنه من] سنين لس[كندر ابن] فليبوس ال[يوناني] ارتسمت انا.....عبد لمسيح (sic)
                      ابن.....سمعان من سب....قسيس ارب (?) يسم.....علي خطيت وانا مسد.....خطي.</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus from="46b"/>
                  <p>On the other side of the same leaf, there is a drawing of a galley.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
